HEADWATERS WIND FARM LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Headwaters Wind Farm LLC ("Headwaters") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Headwaters generating facility ("Headwaters Facility").
The Headwaters Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Randolph County, Indiana. The Headwaters Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Indiana Michigan Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Headwaters' revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Headwaters Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Headwaters' monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Headwaters shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $372,159.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $31,013.25.
